.TH "ata_pci_bmdma_init_one" 9 "ata_pci_bmdma_init_one" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_pci_bmdma_init_one \- Initialize/register BMDMA PCI IDE controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ata_pci_bmdma_init_one
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "const struct ata_port_info * const * ppi "  ","
.BI "struct scsi_host_template *sht "  ","
.BI "void *host_priv "  ","
.BI "int hflags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
Controller to be initialized
.IP "ppi" 12
array of port_info, must be enough for two ports
.IP "sht" 12
scsi_host_template to use when registering the host
.IP "host_priv" 12
host private_data
.IP "hflags" 12
host flags

This function is similar to \fBata_pci_sff_init_one\fP but also
takes care of BMDMA initialization.

LOCKING:
Inherited from PCI layer (may sleep).
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative on errno-based value on error.
